, "id": "bfdab357-b348-987c-b97d-6c304721d355"}, "input": {"input": ["DOXEPIN:Doxepin is a tricyclic antidepressant (TCA) primarily used to treat depression and anxiety disorders. It is well-known for its significant sedative effects, which can be beneficial for patients experiencing sleep disturbances or heightened anxiety. However, Doxepin is also associated with a range of potential side effects, including weight gain, cognitive impairment, dry mouth, constipation, and blurred vision. These side effects are attributed to its high anticholinergic properties. Despite its efficacy in managing mood disorders, the side effect profile of Doxepin necessitates careful consideration and monitoring by healthcare providers when prescribing this medication.", "PAROXETINE:Paroxetine is a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) primarily used as an antidepressant medication to treat significant emotional低落, depression, anxiety disorders, and panic disorders. It is known for its low sedative effect and has a half-life of approximately 20 hours. The typical dosage for Paroxetine starts at 20mg per day, which can be increased up to 50mg per day depending on the patient's needs. It is particularly effective for elderly patients suffering from depression and anxiety. While Paroxetine is considered safe in cases of overdose, it may cause side effects such as gastrointestinal symptoms and insomnia. Overall, Paroxetine is a widely used and effective medication for managing various mood and anxiety-related conditions.", "SERTRALINE:Sertraline is a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) primarily used in the treatment of depression, anxiety, and obsessive-compulsive disorder. As a newer antidepressant, it is known for having relatively milder side effects compared to older drugs in its class. Sertraline has a moderate half-life of approximately 25 hours, making it suitable for once-daily administration. It is typically initiated at a dose of 50mg per day, which can be adjusted up to 150mg per day based on the patient's clinical response and tolerance. The medication can be taken either in the morning or evening, depending on patient preference and side effect profile. While Sertraline is considered safe in cases of overdose, it may cause side effects such as gastrointestinal symptoms and insomnia. Its efficacy in addressing depression and suicidal ideation has made it a widely prescribed option in psychiatric treatment.", "CITALOPRAM:Citalopram is a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) primarily used in the treatment of depression, including cases involving suicidal ideation. It is also effective in managing anxiety disorders, alcohol dependence, and premenstrual dysphoric disorder. Citalopram is characterized by a very low sedative effect and a half-life of approximately 35 hours, which contributes to its stable therapeutic profile. The typical dosage ranges from 10-20 mg per day, with the possibility of increasing up to 40 mg per day as needed. One of its advantages is its minimal interaction with liver cytochrome P450 enzymes, making it a suitable option for combination therapy with other medications. While Citalopram is generally considered safe in cases of overdose, it may cause side effects such as gastrointestinal symptoms and insomnia. Overall, Citalopram is a widely used and versatile antidepressant with a favorable safety profile.", "FLUVOXAMINE:Fluvoxamine is a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) primarily used to treat depression and obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD). It is characterized by a moderate sedative effect, with mild sedative and hypnotic properties, making it typically administered in the evening. The medication has a half-life of approximately 15 hours. Fluvoxamine is generally initiated at a dose of 50mg per day, which can be adjusted and increased up to a maximum of 300mg per day, depending on the patient's response and tolerance. While it is considered safe in cases of overdose, it may cause side effects such as gastrointestinal symptoms and insomnia. Overall, Fluvoxamine is a well-established treatment option for managing depression and OCD, with a balanced profile of efficacy and tolerability.", "TRAZODONE:Trazodone is an antidepressant known for its unique mechanism of action, distinguishing it from other medications in its class. It is primarily used to treat depression and is also effective in managing insomnia due to its high sedative effects. Trazodone has a relatively short half-life, ranging from 6 to 11 hours, which influences its dosing frequency. While it is considered safe in overdose, it has a wide dose range that requires careful titration to achieve therapeutic effects. One notable side effect of Trazodone is cognitive impairment, which may occur in some patients. Overall, Trazodone is a versatile medication with both antidepressant and sedative properties, making it a valuable option for individuals with co-occurring depression and sleep disturbances.", "MIANSERIN:Mianserin is an antidepressant with a different mechanism of action. It is safe in overdose but has a wide dose range and can cause cognitive impairment.", "VENLAFAXINE:Venlafaxine is a newer antidepressant medication classified as a serotonin-norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor (SNRI). It is primarily indicated for the treatment of depression, including cases involving suicidal ideation, and is also effective in managing anxiety disorders. Venlafaxine works by inhibiting the reuptake of both serotonin and norepinephrine, which helps improve mood and attention. Compared to older antidepressant drugs, it is associated with relatively milder side effects and has a rapid onset of action. However, at high doses, it can cause sustained hypertension, necessitating careful monitoring. Venlafaxine has a short half-life of 3-5 hours, which may require more frequent dosing to maintain therapeutic levels. Overall, it is recognized for its good safety profile and efficacy in treating depressive and anxiety-related conditions.", "MIRTAZAPINE:Mirtazapine is a newer antidepressant classified as a Noradrenergic and Specific Serotonergic Antidepressant (NaSSA), known for its dual action on norepinephrine and serotonin. It is primarily used in the treatment of depression, including cases involving suicidal ideation, and is also effective in managing insomnia due to its high sedative effects. Mirtazapine has a half-life of 20-40 hours, contributing to its sustained therapeutic action. While it is recognized for its good safety profile, common side effects include weight gain and drowsiness. Overall, Mirtazapine is a versatile medication that addresses both depressive symptoms and sleep disturbances, making it a valuable option in psychiatric treatment.", "NE & 5-HT REUPTAKE INHIBITORS (SNRIS):"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}